---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const BOT_USERNAME = '@argostherobot';
const REMIX_LINK = 'https://www.val.town/x/brian1/Argos';
---

<BaseLayout
  theme="experiments"
  activeSlug="experiments"
  title="Argos — Phone That Cares About You"
  showComments={false}
>
  <article class="telegram-bot-page">
    <header class="intro">
      <p class="kicker">
        <a href="/experiments">← Experiments</a> · Experiment 03
      </p>
      <h1>Argos</h1>
      <p class="lede">
        Argos is designed to be something like a minimum viable personal assistant, adding capabilities as it knows more about you. With just your name, your timezone, and a few things you love, it sends you a small offering of art it thinks you'd like each morning. If you turn on the morning check-in, it becomes a journal that talks back, and starts learning about you naturally. If you want to paste in old journals, export your bookmarks, or tell it about your people, it'll build these things out into a whole library of you, sorted into views you might find useful.
      </p>

      <figure class="hero">
        <img
          src="/experiments/telegram-bot.jpg"
          alt="Argos — a Telegram companion bot"
        />
      </figure>
    </header>

    <section aria-labelledby="what-it-does">
      <h2 id="what-it-does">What it does</h2>
      <ul class="feature-list">
        <li><strong>Text + voice + photos.</strong> Talk to it however feels easiest. Voice notes get transcribed; photos get looked at.</li>
        <li><strong>Memory.</strong> Tell it what to remember (a name, a preference, a thing about you) and it'll carry that forward.</li>
        <li><strong>Reminders.</strong> "Ping me at 6 about the thing." It will.</li>
        <li><strong>Web search.</strong> It can look things up when the answer isn't in its head.</li>
        <li><strong>Optional morning check-ins.</strong> A short message in the morning if you want one — off by default.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section aria-labelledby="hosted">
      <h2 id="hosted">Try the hosted version</h2>
      <p>
        Easiest path. Open Telegram, find <code>{BOT_USERNAME}</code>, send
        anything. It'll reply.
      </p>

      <div class="cta-card">
        <a class="download-button" href={`https://t.me/${BOT_USERNAME.replace('@','')}`} target="_blank" rel="noopener">
          Open {BOT_USERNAME} in Telegram <span class="arrow">→</span>
        </a>
        <p class="install-note">
          <strong>On privacy:</strong> messages flow through my OpenAI
          account, not yours — that's why you don't need a key. Tradeoff:
          I can technically see what you send. I won't snoop, but I could,
          so know that. If you'd rather own the whole pipeline, the
          self-host path is right below.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section aria-labelledby="self-host">
      <h2 id="self-host">Self-host your own copy</h2>
      <p>
        About thirty minutes, no servers to babysit. Your data lives in
        your account, your bot listens to your token, and the model calls
        run through your own keys. Walk through the steps in order.
      </p>

      <ol class="journey">
        <li>
          <span class="step-num">01</span>
          <div class="step-body">
            <p class="step-title">Sign up for Val.town</p>
            <p>Val.town is where the bot's brain runs. Free account, takes 30 seconds. <a href="https://val.town" target="_blank" rel="noopener">val.town</a> → sign in with Google or GitHub.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="step-num">02</span>
          <div class="step-body">
            <p class="step-title">Remix the bot</p>
            <p>Once you're signed in, hit the button below. It copies the bot into your account.</p>
            <p><a class="download-button" href={REMIX_LINK} target="_blank" rel="noopener">Remix the bot <span class="arrow">→</span></a></p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="step-num">03</span>
          <div class="step-body">
            <p class="step-title">Open your new val's URL</p>
            <p>After remixing, Val.town drops you into your new copy. Click <code>main.ts</code> in the sidebar, hit <em>Run</em>, and a public URL appears at the top. Open that URL in a new tab — the rest of the steps live there.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="step-num">04</span>
          <div class="step-body">
            <p class="step-title">Make a Telegram bot</p>
            <p>Open <a href="https://t.me/BotFather" target="_blank" rel="noopener">@BotFather</a> in Telegram, send <code>/newbot</code>, follow the prompts. It'll hand you a token. Copy it.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="step-num">05</span>
          <div class="step-body">
            <p class="step-title">Paste the token</p>
            <p>On your val's setup page (the tab from step 3), there's a form. Paste the token, click <em>set up bot</em>.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="step-num">06</span>
          <div class="step-body">
            <p class="step-title">Message your bot</p>
            <p>Open Telegram, find your new bot, send anything. It'll lock to your chat and reply. Text or voice both work.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="step-num">07</span>
          <div class="step-body">
            <p class="step-title">Use it</p>
            <p>That's the whole thing. Talk to it. It remembers what you ask it to remember.</p>
            <p>Commands: <code>/help</code> · <code>/morning</code> · <code>/evening</code> · <code>/connect &lt;name&gt;</code> · <code>/memory</code> · <code>/settings</code> · <code>/forget</code> · <code>/reset</code></p>
          </div>
        </li>
      </ol>
    </section>

    <section class="credit" aria-labelledby="credit">
      <h2 id="credit">Credit</h2>
      <p>
        Based on patterns from
        <a href="https://github.com/tasshin/mentor-mock" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Tasshin Fogleman's mentor-mock</a>
        (MIT). The conceptual lineage — a bot that's a companion rather
        than a tool, that remembers, that's quietly there — is his. See
        also <a href="https://tasshin.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">tasshin.com</a>.
      </p>
    </section>

  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .telegram-bot-page {
    max-width: 680px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 24px;
  }

  .intro {
    margin-bottom: 3.5rem;
  }

  .kicker {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .kicker a {
    color: inherit;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
    padding-bottom: 1px;
  }

  .intro h1 {
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  .lede {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .hero {
    margin: 0;
  }

  .hero img {
    display: block;
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    border-radius: 6px;
    border: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
  }

  section {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
    padding-top: 2.25rem;
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
  }

  section h2 {
    font-size: clamp(1.25rem, 2.6vw, 1.6rem);
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
    line-height: 1.25;
  }

  section p {
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin: 1rem 0;
  }

  .feature-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 1rem 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.85rem;
  }

  .feature-list li {
    line-height: 1.6;
    padding-left: 1.1rem;
    position: relative;
  }

  .feature-list li::before {
    content: '·';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    top: -0.05em;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  code {
    font-family: 'SF Mono', Menlo, Consolas, monospace;
    font-size: 0.85em;
    background: rgba(43, 43, 34, 0.06);
    padding: 1px 6px;
    border-radius: 3px;
  }

  em {
    font-style: normal;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .cta-card {
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
    padding: 1.5rem 1.75rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
    border-radius: 6px;
    background: rgba(43, 43, 34, 0.025);
  }

  .download-button {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--accent);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
    padding-bottom: 2px;
    transition: border-color 150ms ease, gap 150ms ease;
  }

  .download-button:hover {
    border-color: var(--accent);
  }

  .download-button:hover .arrow {
    transform: translateX(2px);
  }

  .arrow {
    display: inline-block;
    transition: transform 200ms ease;
  }

  .install-note {
    margin-top: 0.9rem;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.65;
  }

  .install-note strong {
    color: var(--text-primary);
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .journey {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 1.5rem 0 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1.6rem;
  }

  .journey li {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 2.4rem 1fr;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    align-items: baseline;
  }

  .journey .step-num {
    font-family: 'SF Mono', Menlo, Consolas, monospace;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    padding-top: 0.15em;
  }

  .journey .step-title {
    font-weight: 500;
    margin: 0 0 0.45rem;
    font-size: 1.02rem;
  }

  .journey .step-body p {
    margin: 0.5rem 0 0;
    line-height: 1.65;
  }

  .journey .step-body p:first-child {
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  .credit p {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }
</style>
